  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Partial thickness burns are a common, painful injury requiring a great deal of resources in
      their care. Silver sulfadizine is a commonly-used topical antimicrobial, but is difficult to
      remove due to its lipid base. We are comparing a water-based topical antimicrobial therapy to
      silver sulfadiazine and hypothesize that the water-based therapy is superior in terms of pain
      control and resources required to deliver care.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
